PHASE 1: Educational Preference & Control Implementations
------------------------------------------------------------
============================================================
BASIC PREFERENCE VECTORS (C VECTORS)
============================================================
Preference vectors encode what the agent wants to observe.
Higher values = more preferred observations.

Food Preference Examples:
Observations: ['Bitter', 'Neutral', 'Sweet', 'Very Sweet']

Sweet Tooth:
  Bitter      : 0.0
  Neutral     : 1.0
  Sweet       : 3.0
  Very Sweet  : 5.0
  Preference probs: [0.00580663 0.01578405 0.11662925 0.86178007]
  Most preferred: Very Sweet

Health Conscious:
  Bitter      : 0.0
  Neutral     : 2.0
  Sweet       : 1.0
  Very Sweet  : 0.0
  Preference probs: [0.08259454 0.61029569 0.22451524 0.08259454]
  Most preferred: Neutral

Bitter Lover:
  Bitter      : 3.0
  Neutral     : 1.0
  Sweet       : 0.0
  Very Sweet  : 0.0
  Preference probs: [0.80977599 0.10959126 0.04031637 0.04031637]
  Most preferred: Bitter

Indifferent:
  Bitter      : 1.0
  Neutral     : 1.0
  Sweet       : 1.0
  Very Sweet  : 1.0
  Preference probs: [0.25 0.25 0.25 0.25]
  Most preferred: Bitter

Key insights:
- Higher C values = stronger preferences
- C vectors can encode any preference pattern
- Softmax converts preferences to probability distributions

============================================================
EFE-BASED ACTION SELECTION
============================================================
Actions are selected to minimize Expected Free Energy (EFE).
EFE = Pragmatic Value + Epistemic Value
Example: Robot navigation with PyMDP EFE computation.

PyMDP Model Validation:
A matrix normalized: True
B matrix normalized: True
Model structure valid: True

