✅ COMPREHENSIVE TAKEAWAYS: PREFERENCES & CONTROL WITH PYMDP INTEGRATION
================================================================================
🎯 PREFERENCE-DRIVEN CONTROL FOUNDATIONS:
1. Expected Free Energy (EFE) = Pragmatic Value + Epistemic Value
2. Lower EFE = Better policy (minimizes surprise + maximizes preferences)
3. Pragmatic value captures preference satisfaction (-E[C])
4. Epistemic value captures information gain (exploration drive)
5. EFE naturally balances exploitation (pragmatic) vs exploration (epistemic)
6. Control as inference: minimize EFE to achieve desired outcomes

🚀 PYMDP AGENT INTEGRATION:
7. C vectors seamlessly integrate with PyMDP Agent class
8. Agent.infer_policies() uses C vectors for preference-driven behavior
9. Multi-step policies enable complex goal-directed sequences
10. Different preference profiles lead to different behavioral strategies
11. PyMDP construct_policies() generates all possible policy sequences
12. Softmax over negative EFE gives probabilistic action selection

